    "narrative": "For the April 9th slate, the Zurich Zebras lean heavily on table-setters at the top of the order to maximize our 5x5 Roto upside. **Colt Keith** (66.33) anchors our lineup as the highest-projected start today; his promotion to the leadoff spot against Abel provides a significant +10% efficiency bump, combined with favorable park factors that push his base projection into the Strong category. **Chase Meidroth** (62.08) similarly capitalizes on a high-leverage leadoff role against Lugo. While we are monitoring the wind out at the venue\u2014providing a +5% boost to his raw output\u2014the matchup against a 4.53 xERA arm allows both **Colt Keith** and **Chase Meidroth** to operate with high floor security, even as we remain mindful of the minor -4% penalty **Chase Meidroth** carries for a slightly sub-optimal dynamic platoon split today.\n\nThe broader roster landscape remains static as several core assets, including **Yordan Alvarez**, **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Trea Turner**, are sidelined by a team-wide off-day. This absence leaves our bench depth untested today, but ensures we avoid burning daily game caps on replacement-level options. With the rest of our core\u2014including **Kyle Schwarber**, **Christian Yelich**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Zac Veen**, **Victor Scott II**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Logan O'Hoppe**, **Josh Smith**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Carson Benge**, and **Luis Pena**\u2014resting or inactive, the focus remains entirely on the high-probability production expected from our two active starters. As we approach first pitch, no weather hazards have been flagged, but the lack of secondary hitting options dictates a conservative management strategy to preserve our limited game inventory for higher-upside matchups later in the week.",
